  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into discs</p><p>Add the <strong>potato discs</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until the potatoes are golden and crispy – these are your <strong>crispy potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1682082755897-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1682082755897-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1682082755897-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1682082755897-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1682082755897-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, chop your <strong>Tenderstem broccoli </strong>in half</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>red onion[s] </strong>into wedges and peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Zest <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lemon[s] </strong>(try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter)</p><p>Take 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>butter</strong> out of the fridge and set aside to warm up</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1682082760662-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1682082760662-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1682082760662-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1682082760662-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1682082760662-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>halved Tenderstem broccoli</strong> and <strong>onion wedges </strong>to a separate baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-12 min or until tender, golden and crisp – this is your <strong>roasted veg</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1682082765978-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1682082765978-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1682082765978-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1682082765978-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1682082765978-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the veg is cooking, combine your <strong>balsamic sun-dried tomato paste</strong> with the <strong>softened butter</strong>, <strong>lemon zest </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) in a bowl</p><p>Tip: If your butter is not soft then microwave for a few secs or until soft to the touch but not melted!</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>sun-dried tomato butter</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1682082769746-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1682082769746-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1682082769746-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1682082769746-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1682082769746-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>remaining garlic </strong>(not a big garlic fan? Try using less!),<strong> </strong>1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> cold water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a small bowl – this is your <strong>aioli</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
